 New Roman&quot;;
mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi">The purpose of this study is to assess the
amount of noise generated in FFT processing when using FP16 data and
coefficient formats, measure the noise with respect of the amplitude and
spectral content, measure the noise with respect to the FFT length. Propose
simple solutions to improve the computation results.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:1=
2.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times=
 New Roman&quot;;
mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi">The program has 4 parameters: 1)&nbsp;input
FP32, mono, file name, raw format; 2) output file name after FFT and cascad=
ed
inverse FFT in FP32; 3) output file name for the same processing in FP16; 4=
)
the log2 of the FFT length (must stay &lt;=3D 14)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

